HEADWORD: Revision
<hw>Re*vi"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>r⟦eacute⟧vision</ets>, L. revisio.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act
of revising; reexamination for correction; review; <as>as, the
<ex>revision</ex> of a book or writing, or of a proof sheet; a
<ex>revision</ex> of statutes.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is made by revising.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Reexamination; revisal; revise; review.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Revisionary</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Revisional</ent>⟦br⟧
